				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Panzer Kids Deluxe: Easy Wargame Rules for Quick Tank Battles with Optional Rules &amp; Source Material" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Panzer Kids Deluxe contains all the basic rules to run simple tabletop skirmishes between World War II tanks. You provide the miniatures, dice, and terrain. The rules outline how to set up the battlefield, deploy your tanks, move them to get the best shots on opponents while taking advantage of cover, and attack!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This deluxe version includes:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     the core basic rules plus&amp;#10;     Optional rules for wrecks, flanking shots, damage effects, close range combat, hull-down deployment, hull-mounted guns, anti-tank guns, elite units, road movement, mine fields, objective, and moving objectives.&amp;#10;     Brief descriptions and game stats for numerous tanks, self-propelled guns, and anti-tank guns from the United Kingdom, France, Italy, Germany, the Soviet Union, and the United States.&amp;#10;     Guidelines for creating your own historical tank stats.&amp;#10;     Four historical scenarios. &amp;ldquo;Tetrarchs in the Forest,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Vichy&amp;rsquo;s Last Charge,&amp;rdquo; &amp;ldquo;Rommel at Arras,&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Hellcats at the Bulge.&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Panzer Kids introduces wargaming newcomers to fundamental elements like movement, range, line of sight, cover, and casualties. Appropriate for adults interested in learning about miniature wargames or introducing children to the hobby.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
